Here’s the link for vouchers - these are 100% going to sell out so get in quick. https://finns.to/SagQ3
I’ve got mine - I’ll see you in Bali! 
Follow @finnsbeachclub for more info.

Cloud iridescence usually happens in altocumulus, cirrocumulus, lenticular and cirrus clouds. Iridescent clouds happen because of diffraction – a phenomenon that occurs when small water droplets or small ice crystals scatter the sun’s light.

Spotting the rare pink dolphin 🐬💖

While we’re not sure whether this video was edited or not, pink dolphins actually exist. The endangered Amazon river dolphin and Indo-Pacific humpback dolphin both have a pink shade to them (especially males). Have you heard of them before?

via @discoverwildlife
